 In order to draw a picture, one can make use of the simple pencil. One can make use of the simple pencil by using either the sharpened tip, which can be obtained by removing the wood component, or the mechanical component to create a point, or the simple lead in the mechanical component, which can be obtained by pulling the wire component. The simple lead can be obtained by allowing the mechanical component to be pressed against the wood component. Once sufficiently ripped, the simple lead can be obtained
